    <main id="main">
      <div id="title">Oprah Gail Winfrey</div>
      <!-- White background header START -->
      <div id="header">
      <div id="img-div">
        <img id="image" src="https://www.amacad.org/sites/default/files/person/headshots/oprah.jpg"/>
        <div id="img-caption">
        <h4>Oprah Winfrey is a media mogul, talk show host, and philanthropist known for her influential impact on television and her dedication to empowering others through charitable work.</h4>
        </div>
        </div>
      </div> <!-- White background header END -->
    <div id="tribute-info">
      <h3 id="headline">Here's a timeline of Oprah Gail Winfrey's life to date:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>1954</strong>
            - Born on January 29th in Kosciusko, Mississippi.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>1971</strong> - Wins Miss Black Tennessee beauty pageant at 17.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>1976</strong> - Starts broadcasting career and becomes the first African-American female news anchor.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>1986</strong> - "The Oprah Winfrey Show" debuts nationally in syndication.
          </li>
         <li>
            <strong>1988</strong> - Establishes Harpo Productions, her multimedia company.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>1996</strong> - Launches Oprah's Book Club, influencing book sales worldwide.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2005</strong> - Becomes the first African-American woman listed as a billionaire by Forbes.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2011</strong> - Ends "The Oprah Winfrey Show" after 25 successful years.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2013</strong> - Receives the Presidential Medal of Freedom.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2018</strong> - Delivers a powerful speech at the Golden Globe Awards.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Present</strong> - Oprah continues to maintain her status as one of the most influential and respected figures in the entertainment industry.
          </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div id="tribute-quote">
      <p>"Oprah Winfrey represents the most ingenious and creative expression of black spiritual genius in the public mainstream that we've had in quite a long time, if ever."</p>
      <p>-- Michael Eric Dyson (Academic, Author, Minister.)</p>
    </div>
    <div id="footer-link">
      <h3>If you have time, you should read more about this incredible woman on her <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oprah_Winfrey">Wikipedia entry.</h3>
    </div>
    </main>
  </body>
